Dancer advent calendar 2018 - The Twelve Days of Dancer!

Article suggestions / volunteers to write them very much appreciated.

This is the current state of the 2018 Advent Calendar. A few things have
yet to be confirmed, so this list may go through another iteration or two.

If you have ideas or want to volunteer, find us in irc.perl.org/#dancer, or
email the dancer-users mailing list, or contact cromedome@cpan.org - thanks!

The Twelve Days of Dancer (starting December 13th):
13 - State of the Dancer (cromedome)
14 - Dancer Survey Result Recap (cromedome)
15 - Dancer2::Plugin::Paginator (manwar)
16 - Dancer2 and Minion (cromedome)
17 - Dancer and Email (racke)
18 - Subclassing the Dancer CLI (Sawyer)
19 - Logging with Dancer2::Logger::Log4perl (cromedome)
20 - Testing Dancer2 apps with Test::Mojo (Joel Berger)
21 - Using Dancer2::Logger::Console::Colored (simbabque)
22 - ParamTypes, Part I & II (Sawyer)
23 - Spam and bot prevention without the use of CAPTCHAs (cromedome)
24 - The future of Dancer (I can speak to projects I have in the works, but we can all collaborate on this one)

For next year's calendar...

Flags: 

[ ] : up for adoption
[A] : "Assigned", someone volunteered to write it
[P] : "Pending", someone started writing that article
[R] : "Review", ready for review (needs typos fixes and proofreading)
[D] : "Done", ready for publication
[L] : "Last Review", reviewed but still some things left undone

